cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the task of synaptic connectivity detection using deep neural networks. The proposed method involves the use of 3D U-net and 3D CNN for predicting the location and direction of both dyadic and polyadic synapses. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques for pruning the set of candidates, which suggests the involvement of neural networks for optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for synapse detection, which suggests the involvement of cs.LG (Learning). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques for predicting the location and direction of synapses, which suggests the involvement of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for image analysis, which suggests the involvement of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
